Few hours after receiving the Certificate of Return from the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC), Senator Hope Uzodinma, has been sworn in as the Governor of Imo State. Uzodinma was sworn in by the Chief Judge of the state, Paschal Nnadi, on Wednesday evening. This is barely twenty-four hours after a seven-man panel of the Supreme Court declared him the winner of the election held in March 2019. Imo: APC governors congratulate Senator Uzodinma #SupremeCourt: Uzodinma’s catapult to first place shocking ―… Senate President congratulates APC, Imo Governor-elect INEC releases time table for re-run, supplementary elections… The former Chairman, Senate Committee on Customs took the oath of office and allegiance at about 7:28 pm before a mammoth crowd at the Heroes Square Arena, in Owerri, the state capital. ALSO READ: We will pursue Amotekun to logical conclusion ― Akeredolu He thereafter signed the required documents empowering him as the seventh governor of the state. His deputy, Placid Njoku, also took the oath of office and allegiance at 7:18 pm. Dignitaries at the event include the National Chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Adams Oshiohmole, former governor of the state, Rochas Okorocha. among others. STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO  WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS FREE